## 12.17 The reflex

When you know what you want but not the name:

1. `(apropos \"keyword\")` — try the name first
2. `(doc-search \"keyword\")` — try the docs if the name search was thin
3. `(verbs-in-namespace \"ns\")` — try the namespace if you know the family
4. `(did-you-mean 'guess)` — LLM-augmented for tricky cases (Chapter 13)

Four options. Try them in order. One of them will hit.

## 12.18 A worked example

You want to compute standard deviation. You do not remember what Motoi calls it.

```scheme
(apropos \"dev\")
;; => (deviate std-dev standard-deviation mean-abs-dev)
```

Three candidates. Which one?

```scheme
(describe 'std-dev)
;; std-dev [math] — arity 1
;; Return the standard deviation of a list of numbers.
```

Perfect. Copy from `(examples-of 'std-dev)`, adapt, done.

Two searches, one describe, one examples. From *I need standard deviation* to *I have a working call* in four keystrokes.

